RIYADH: Saudi Arabian budget airline flynas has announced the launch of its first direct flights from Riyadh to Podgorica, the capital of Montenegro, starting July 28. It will connect Riyadh and Podgorica via weekly direct return flights, scheduled every Thursday, from King Khalid International Airport in Riyadh to Podgorica International Airport, the airlines said in a press release. Current rules will allow Saudi nationals to enter Montenegro without a visa until Sept. 30, 2022, it added. flynas recently partnered with Amazon Payment Services to offer installment payment options to customers, thus becoming the first carrier in the Kingdom to offer this facility.